    Immunological Biomarker Discovery in Cure Regimens for Chronic Hepatitis B Virus Infection.
This paper will discuss the importance of sample collection, the assays available for immunological analyses, their advantages/disadvantages and suggestions for their implementation in clinical trials. Careful consideration must be given to ensure appropriate immunological studies are included as a primary component of the trial with deeper immunological analysis provided by ancillary studies. Standardizing immunological assays and data obtained from clinical trials will identify biomarkers that can be deployed in the clinic, independent of specialized immunology laboratories.
